From its origins as an online bookstore, Amazon has grown into grocery deliveries,

7
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:34,000
TV and music streaming and even space exploration.

8
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:38,000
Making its founder Jeff Bezos the richest person on earth.

9
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:43,000
Amazon is so successful it affects how many of us live our lives.

10
00:00:43,000 --> 00:00:49,000
So in this program we'll be taking a look inside the brain of Jeff Bezos to find out how he thinks.

11
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:55,000
When Jeff Bezos' friends talk about him three words they often use are

12
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:59,000
invention, risk-taking and long-term vision.

13
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:03,000
These are qualities which Bezos admired in his grandfather Lawrence,

14
00:01:03,000 --> 00:01:09,000
who from an early age taught Jeff that by careful thinking any problem can be solved.

15
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:14,000
As a boy, Jeff and his grandfather repaired an old broken-down truck.

16
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:19,000
When interviewed today, Bezos sometimes compares Amazon to that truck.

17
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:23,000
Very heavy but impossible to stop when it rolls downhill.

18
00:01:23,000 --> 00:01:26,000
Which is exactly what accidentally happened one day.

19
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:30,000
